ENTRY            L0291   20260219   20260422   20260422       L057
SUBENT        L0291001   20260219   20260422   20260422       L057
BIB                 12         35
TITLE      Testing shell-model interactions at high excitation
           energy and low spin: Nuclear resonance fluorescence
           in 74Ge
AUTHOR     (S.R.Johnson,R.V.F.Janssens,U.Friman-Gayer,B.A.Brown,
           B.P.Crider,S.W.Finch,Krishichayan,D.R.Little,
           S.Mukhopadhyay,E.E.Peters,A.P.D.Ramirez,J.A.Silano,
           A.P.Tonchev,W.Tornow,S.W.Yates)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,108,024315,2023)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.108.024315
REL-REF    (R,G0050002,R.Massarczyk+,J,PR/C,92,044309,2015)
INSTITUTE  (1USANCA,1USATNL,1USAMSU,1USAMSS,1USADKE,1USAKTY,
           1USALRL)
FACILITY   (LASER,1USATNL) The Triangle Universities Nuclear
           Laboratory's (TUNL) High-Intensity Gamma-Ray Source
            (HIgS).
INC-SPECT  HIgS provided quasi-monoenergetic, linearly polarized
           gamma-ray beams at 16 energy settings between 3.10
           and 5.44 MeV with a relative full width at half-
           maximum (FWHM) of about 3%.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) The gamma**3 setup at HIgS, consisting of six
           high-purity germanium (HPGe) detectors placed at
           angles suitable to distinguish between photons of
           different multipole character, taking advantage of
           the >99% linear polarization of the beam.
SAMPLE     (32-GE-74,ENR=0.989) The 74Ge target consisted of
           germanium dioxide powder, isotopically enriched to
           98.90(5)%, weighing 8.968(5) g with a thickness of
           1.91 cm.
METHOD     (GSPEC) The target nuclei were excited by the HIgS
           beam and the fluorescent radiation emitted was
           measured. Data were accumulated for 4-6 h at each
           lower energy setting and 6-7 h for each higher energy
           one.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No details on sources of uncertainties.
HISTORY    (20260219C) BP
ENDBIB              35
